<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11134&amp;p=127299#p127299"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />These are amazing... it's like some of the limitations imposed by the video hardware don't even exist!<br /></div><br /><br />Those gears in the third picture make the NES' attribute layout limitation quite obvious.  I never noticed it until someone mentioned it, but NES games seem to use a LOT of black, most likely to compensate for the 16*16 attribute limitation.  These graphics make the limitations much more obvious, unfortunately.<br /><br />I'm not knocking on anyone's talents, though, this looks really good.  I like the use of colors, though some areas are overpowered by the black.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=6132">OneCrudeDude</a> — Mon Mar 31, 2014 12:00 am</p><hr />
